fields.description:
Apparently Webkit has some kind of bug (affects Chrome and Safari).

!http://content.screencast.com/users/AdamAtlassian/folders/Jing/media/bfb3f320-96ba-47a2-ba98-ee47a738b031/Webkit%20fail.png!

There is a css rule {code}
.collapsed-sidebar #branch-selector { display: none; }
{code} that should be applied but is initially ignored.  Eventually the user can interact and cause it to be applied, but it's definitely some kind of quirky bug in the browser.

Hard to say what the fix would be, since doing seemingly unrelated things in the dev tools will cause it to fix itself.  You'll have to do actual {{ant content}} s to be sure you've got it.

The link in the breadcrumb on the changeset page is being escaped too much, escaping the '?' and '=' characters in the link arguments.

!http://img.skitch.com/20101013-g69y3b6qy9bciqs1j234eik46k.jpg!

Example url:
https://extranet.atlassian.com/crucible/changelog/FE-hg/?cs=570d1381d99de3c11fa671d2b094127c92d18fec

The breadcrumb link is
{code}
https://extranet.atlassian.com/crucible/changelog/FE-hg%3Fcsid%3D570d1381d99de3c11fa671d2b094127c92d18fec
{code}

instead of

{code}
https://extranet.atlassian.com/crucible/changelog/FE-hg/?csid=570d1381d99de3c11fa671d2b094127c92d18fec
{code}
